Beginning 2014 - Package previously named script_header_brendlefly
version 0.2.0 added color(), incl reverse video \"\${RVon}\"
 0.2.11, moved bs() and countdown() to the extended function set
 0.3.0 added checkshell() to adjust for non-interactive shells
 0.3.7 updated the swr() function, to use nmap
 0.3.8 moved watchdistcc to dev-util/joetoolkit and added fe()
 0.3.9 moved which() to dev-util/joetoolkit
 0.3.10 updates checkboot() for x86/ x86_64/armv7l/aarch64
 0.4.0 is a major rewrite, consolidating content in FILESDIR
 0.4.1 fixes d_echo() and adds isnumber() and ishex() functions
 0.4.2 fixes isnumber(), ishex(), and d_echo() for busybox (ash shell)
 0.4.3 now uses #!/bin/sh, asigns VERBOSE/verbosity only if null, offers unbold colors
 0.4.4 fixes d_echo and de_echo for null string e.g. d_echo 1
 0.4.5 adds display_vars() and supporting functions get_longest(), echo_n_long()
 0.4.6 fixes bugs
 0.4.7 fixes a bug in display_vars()
 0.4.7 fixes a bug in display_vars()
 0.4.8 adds function initialize_vars()
 0.5.0 moves to myUtilities repo and adds yn var type for display_vars
 0.5.1 fixes bugs in display_ and initialize_vars
 0.5.2 makes (extended) bs() quieter
 0.5.3 fixes a typo in initialize_vars()
 0.5.4 bugfixes initialize_vars() and moves package to dev-util in src repo
 0.5.5/6 refine display_ and initialize_vars
June 2025: Package renamed script_header_joetoo and significantly enhanced
to include command higher level scripting utilities including line processor,
usage, etc in the extended [bash] header and other updates in
the basic [ash] header.  A template script showing how to use these was also
included.  First uploaded as dev-util/script_header_joetoo 24 June 2025
